apiRef.description: The ref object that allows Tree View manipulation. Can be instantiated with useRichTreeViewApiProRef().

canMoveItemToNewPosition.description: Used to determine if a given item can move to some new position.

parameters.name: parameters
parameters.description: The params describing the item re-ordering.

parameters.itemId.name: parameters.itemId
parameters.itemId.description: The id of the item that is being moved to a new position.

parameters.oldPosition.name: parameters.oldPosition
parameters.oldPosition.description: The old position of the item.

parameters.newPosition.name: parameters.newPosition
parameters.newPosition.description: The new position of the item.

boolean.name: boolean
boolean.description: true if the item can move to the new position.

checkboxSelection.description: Whether the Tree View renders a checkbox at the left of its label that allows selecting it.

classes.description: Override or extend the styles applied to the component.

defaultExpandedItems.description: Expanded item ids. Used when the item's expansion is not controlled.

defaultSelectedItems.description: Selected item ids. (Uncontrolled) When multiSelect is true this takes an array of strings; when false (default) a string.

disabledItemsFocusable.description: Whether the items should be focusable when disabled.

domStructure.description: When equal to 'flat', the tree is rendered as a flat list (children are rendered as siblings of their parents). When equal to 'nested', the tree is rendered with nested children (children are rendered inside the groupTransition slot of their children). Nested DOM structure is not compatible with collapse / expansion animations.

expandedItems.description: Expanded item ids. Used when the item's expansion is controlled.

expansionTrigger.description: The slot that triggers the item's expansion when clicked.

getItemChildren.description: Used to determine the children of a given item.

getItemId.description: Used to determine the id of a given item.

getItemLabel.description: Used to determine the string label for a given item.

id.description: This prop is used to help implement the accessibility logic. If you don't provide this prop. It falls back to a randomly generated id.

isItemDisabled.description: Used to determine if a given item should be disabled.

boolean.name: boolean
boolean.description: true if the item should be disabled.

isItemEditable.description: Determine if a given item can be edited.

isItemReorderable.description: Determine if a given item can be reordered.

itemId.name: itemId
itemId.description: The id of the item to check.

boolean.name: boolean
boolean.description: true if the item can be reordered.

isItemSelectionDisabled.description: Used to determine if a given item should have selection disabled.

boolean.name: boolean
boolean.description: true if the item should have selection disabled.

itemChildrenIndentation.description: Horizontal indentation between an item and its children. Examples: 24, "24px", "2rem", "2em".

itemHeight.description: Sets the height in pixel of an item. If not provided, no height restriction is applied to the tree item content element.

itemsReordering.description: If true, the reordering of items is enabled.

multiSelect.description: Whether multiple items can be selected.

onExpandedItemsChange.description: Callback fired when Tree Items are expanded/collapsed.

event.name: event
event.description: The DOM event that triggered the change. Can be null when the change is caused by the publicAPI.setItemExpansion() method.

itemIds.name: itemIds
itemIds.description: The ids of the expanded items.

onItemClick.description: Callback fired when the content slot of a given Tree Item is clicked.

event.name: event
event.description: The DOM event that triggered the change.

itemId.name: itemId
itemId.description: The id of the focused item.

onItemExpansionToggle.description: Callback fired when a Tree Item is expanded or collapsed.

event.name: event
event.description: The DOM event that triggered the change. Can be null when the change is caused by the publicAPI.setItemExpansion() method.

itemId.name: itemId
itemId.description: The itemId of the modified item.

isExpanded.name: isExpanded
isExpanded.description: true if the item has just been expanded, false if it has just been collapsed.

onItemFocus.description: Callback fired when a given Tree Item is focused.

event.name: event
event.description: The DOM event that triggered the change. Warning: This is a generic event not a focus event.

itemId.name: itemId
itemId.description: The id of the focused item.

onItemLabelChange.description: Callback fired when the label of an item changes.

itemId.name: itemId
itemId.description: The id of the item that was edited.

newLabel.name: newLabel
newLabel.description: The new label of the items.

onItemPositionChange.description: Callback fired when a Tree Item is moved in the tree.

parameters.name: parameters
parameters.description: The params describing the item re-ordering.

parameters.itemId.name: parameters.itemId
parameters.itemId.description: The id of the item moved.

parameters.oldPosition.name: parameters.oldPosition
parameters.oldPosition.description: The old position of the item.

parameters.newPosition.name: parameters.newPosition
parameters.newPosition.description: The new position of the item.

onItemSelectionToggle.description: Callback fired when a Tree Item is selected or deselected.

event.name: event
event.description: The DOM event that triggered the change. Can be null when the change is caused by the publicAPI.setItemSelection() method.

itemId.name: itemId
itemId.description: The itemId of the modified item.

isSelected.name: isSelected
isSelected.description: true if the item has just been selected, false if it has just been deselected.

onSelectedItemsChange.description: Callback fired when Tree Items are selected/deselected.

event.name: event
event.description: The DOM event that triggered the change. Can be null when the change is caused by the publicAPI.setItemSelection() method.

itemIds.name: itemIds
itemIds.description: The ids of the selected items. When multiSelect is true, this is an array of strings; when false (default) a string.

selectedItems.description: Selected item ids. (Controlled) When multiSelect is true this takes an array of strings; when false (default) a string.

selectionPropagation.description:
When selectionPropagation.descendants is set to true.
- Selecting a parent selects all its descendants automatically. - Deselecting a parent deselects all its descendants automatically.
When selectionPropagation.parents is set to true.
- Selecting all the descendants of a parent selects the parent automatically. - Deselecting a descendant of a selected parent deselects the parent automatically.
Only works when multiSelect is true. On the <SimpleTreeView />, only the expanded items are considered (since the collapsed item are not passed to the Tree View component at all)

slotProps.description: The props used for each component slot.

sx.description: The system prop that allows defining system overrides as well as additional CSS styles.

virtualization.description: Whether virtualization is enabled. If true, the DOM structure will be set to 'flat'. If true and no itemHeight is provided, a default item height of 32px will be used for calculating the virtualization.

itemDragAndDropOverlay.nodeName: the item's drag and drop overlay element

itemErrorIcon.description: Styles applied to the item's error icon element

itemIconContainer.nodeName: the item's icon container element icon

itemLabelInput.nodeName: the item's label input element (visible only

itemLoadingIcon.description: Styles applied to the item's loading icon element

slotDescriptions.collapseIcon: The default icon used to collapse the item.
slotDescriptions.endIcon: The default icon displayed next to an end item. This is applied to all Tree Items and can be overridden by the TreeItem icon slot prop.
slotDescriptions.expandIcon: The default icon used to expand the item.
slotDescriptions.item: Custom component to render a Tree Item.
